parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause various electrical system malfunctions, including stalling, loss of power, and random activation of horns, lights, and wipers, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences random electrical system malfunctions
such as stalling
loss of power
horn blowing
lights flashing
wipers activating
and door locks malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes do not function properly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Overflow and Rollover Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rollover valve in the fuel tank can cause fuel to overflow when filling up, leading to a fire hazard, and also increases the risk of fuel leakage in the event of a rollover accident, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the filler neck when refueling
fuel overflows onto the vehicle and ground
the automatic shut-off on the pump does not work
fuel gushes out of the vehicle when the pump shuts off
and the check engine light and gas cap light may come on.
